      <data key="d6">company</data>
      <data key="d7">Japanese specialty chemicals company (subsidiary of Ajinomoto Co., Inc.) founded September 1942. Common stock 315M yen, 295 employees (April 2019). HQ in Gunma Prefecture. Operates three divisions: Electronic Materials (ABF), Functional Materials (adhesives, dispersing agents, one-component epoxy resin curing agents, flame retardants), and Activated Carbon. Producer of Ajinomoto Build-up Film (ABF), the dominant interlayer insulating film for semiconductor packaging substrates globally since 1999.</data>
