    <node id="dram_manufacture_flow_diagram">
      <data key="d6">process_diagram</data>
      <data key="d0">DRAM Manufacture Flow (Introduction)</data>
      <data key="d7">Process-flow illustration titled '(2) Introduction to DRAM Manufacture Flow' showing sequential steps: wafers/silicon crystal -&gt; Mask 1 -&gt; N-Well Implant -&gt; Oxidation Furnace -&gt; LPCVD Furnace -&gt; Mask 2 -&gt; Oxidation Furnace x3 -&gt; LPCVD Furnace -&gt; Mask 3 -&gt; Plasma Etch -&gt; LPCVD Furnace -&gt; One Furnace -&gt; LPCVD Furnace -&gt; Mask 4 -&gt; P+ Implant -&gt; Mask 5 -&gt; N+ Implant -&gt; LPCVD Furnace -&gt; APCVD -&gt; Mask 6 -&gt; Mask 7 -&gt; Metal Sputter -&gt; Mask 8 -&gt; PECVD -&gt; Repeat 7-a to 7-d -&gt; Metal Sputter -&gt; Mask 10 -&gt; PECVD -&gt; Mask 11 -&gt; Alloy Furnace -&gt; Wafer Probe.</data>
